description:
Your identity may not be as safe as you think it is!  Rachel will take you through the threats in our digital world, and show us how to protect yourself from identity theft and other cyber-crime. What We'll Cover:
How your information is used by companies, and how it may be vulnerable;
What new technologies and programs are exposing you to unknown risk;
Examples of everyday identity theft and the consequences to its victims;
Evaluation of your current state of security and an audit of your public information;
Ways to protect yourself and tighten your personal security.
This class is great for people with all levels of experience with technology and the internet, from novice internet users to digital natives!

For the holidays (or just for the heck of it!), spice up your gift-giving or entertaining repertoire with delectable, customized bitters and alcoholic infusions!  Add pizazz to a caesar or champagne with your home-made bitters, or amp up a gin and tonic or eggnog with delectably infused liquor.

This will be a make-along class, where students experiment with their own flavorings and take home product for future gift-giving or imbibing!
What We'll Cover:

How to set up and process your materials for best results;
Different techniques for infusing;
How to select flavours for optimal outcomes;
Troubleshooting issues;
Different recipes for infusions and cocktails made from them.


Attendees at this event must be 19 years of age or older.  Skilltree reserves the right to I.D.
